{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 1972, "title": "Remove deprecated functions", "body": "Remove deprecated functions.\r\nUse tmpdir for export tests.\r\n\r\nAll of the removed functions were deprecated prior to v2.2.0 or earlier.  \r\n\r\nI did not remove `Assembly.save` and the old `Workplane` boolean operator overloads.  These were more recently deprecated Aug 2024 prior to v2.5.0.  \r\n\r\nCloses #680, #1509\r\n", "baseRefName": "master", "baseRefOid": "e486f43256c686d906e22e39135f84deaec05a60", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "CadQuery/cadquery"}, "url": "https://github.com/CadQuery/cadquery/pull/1972", "createdAt": "2026-01-17T23:38:16Z", "mergedAt": "2026-01-19T13:50:59Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "CadQuery/cadquery"}, "sha": "e486f43256c686d906e22e39135f84deaec05a60"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/CadQuery/cadquery/pull/1972.diff", "number": 1972, "created_at": "2026-01-17T23:38:16Z", "merged_at": "2026-01-19T13:50:59Z", "resolved_issues": [680]}
{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 1779, "title": "Add STEP Import for Assemblies", "body": "The goal is to make it possible to round-trip assemblies to and from STEP without loss of data. This data can include:\r\n\r\n* [x] Part location\r\n* [x] Part color\r\n* [x] Shape colors\r\n* [x] Shape colors\r\n* [x] Shape names (advanced face)\r\n\r\nFixes #826 and #1427", "baseRefName": "master", "baseRefOid": "8431073e595871e16470d1a9d8dc5ee184ea1874", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "CadQuery/cadquery"}, "url": "https://github.com/CadQuery/cadquery/pull/1779", "createdAt": "2025-02-26T16:36:44Z", "mergedAt": "2025-10-01T18:38:37Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "CadQuery/cadquery"}, "sha": "8431073e595871e16470d1a9d8dc5ee184ea1874"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/CadQuery/cadquery/pull/1779.diff", "number": 1779, "created_at": "2025-02-26T16:36:44Z", "merged_at": "2025-10-01T18:38:37Z", "resolved_issues": [826]}
{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 1904, "title": "Fix bug in mirrorX and mirrorY", "body": "This should close #1015 \r\n\r\nAnother user ran into this bug. Consider the following.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nPROFILE_OUTER = [\r\n    (10,  0),\r\n    ( 8,  8),\r\n    ( 0, 10),\r\n]\r\n\r\nPROFILE_INNER = [\r\n    ( 1, 1),\r\n    ( 9, 1),\r\n    ( 9, 9),\r\n    ( 1, 9),\r\n]\r\n\r\n# Do the mirroring, but stop after the bugged mirrorY call\r\nterrain = (cq.Workplane(\"XY\")\r\n        .polyline(PROFILE_OUTER)\r\n        .mirrorX()\r\n        .mirrorY()\r\n        .extrude(1)\r\n        .faces(\">Z\")\r\n        .workplane()\r\n        .polyline(PROFILE_INNER)\r\n        .close()\r\n        .extrude(2))\r\n\r\nshow_object(terrain)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAt present, the following is produced because of the mirror bug:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"919\" height=\"771\" alt=\"Screenshot from 2025-09-30 09-21-36\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6a711e88-9239-4312-89a4-918c84e48545\" />\r\n\r\nBut with the fix in this PR, the object will now look like this:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"916\" height=\"813\" alt=\"Screenshot from 2025-09-30 09-20-12\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3b0be61b-7a3c-44a4-b363-1dce12388f99\" />\r\n\r\n", "baseRefName": "master", "baseRefOid": "d33816099adbc88e9be8ab46c091cff11e2665fa", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "CadQuery/cadquery"}, "url": "https://github.com/CadQuery/cadquery/pull/1904", "createdAt": "2025-09-30T13:22:40Z", "mergedAt": "2025-10-02T00:30:13Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "CadQuery/cadquery"}, "sha": "d33816099adbc88e9be8ab46c091cff11e2665fa"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/CadQuery/cadquery/pull/1904.diff", "number": 1904, "created_at": "2025-09-30T13:22:40Z", "merged_at": "2025-10-02T00:30:13Z", "resolved_issues": [1015]}
